## 1. üóÑÔ∏è Database Setup (Supabase - Free & Easy)

### Step 1: Create Supabase Account
1. Go to [supabase.com](https://supabase.com)
2. Click "Start your project" 
3. Sign up with GitHub/Google
4. Create a new project:
   - **Project name**: `rize-job-portal`
   - **Database password**: Choose a strong password
   - **Region**: Choose closest to your users

### Step 2: Get Database Connection Details
1. In your Supabase dashboard, go to **Settings** ‚Üí **Database**
2. Copy the connection details:
   ```
   Host: db.xxx.supabase.co
   Database: postgres
   Username: postgres
   Password: [your-password]
   Port: 5432
   ```

### Step 3: Update Your .env File
```env
# Database Configuration (Supabase)
DB_HOST=db.xxx.supabase.co
DB_PORT=5432
DB_NAME=postgres
DB_USER=postgres
DB_PASSWORD=your_supabase_password
DB_URL=postgresql://postgres:your_supabase_password@db.xxx.supabase.co:5432/postgres
```

### Alternative: Railway (Also Free)
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app)
2. Sign up with GitHub
3. Create new project ‚Üí Add PostgreSQL
4. Copy connection URL from dashboard

