## 6. üöÄ Deployment Platform Setup

### Option A: Vercel (Recommended for Node.js)

#### Step 1: Install Vercel CLI
```bash
npm i -g vercel
```

#### Step 2: Deploy
```bash
vercel login
vercel --prod
```

#### Step 3: Set Environment Variables
1. Go to your Vercel dashboard
2. Select your project
3. Go to **Settings** ‚Üí **Environment Variables**
4. Add all variables from your .env file

### Option B: Railway (Full-Stack Friendly)

#### Step 1: Connect GitHub
1. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app)
2. Sign up with GitHub
3. Create new project from GitHub repo

#### Step 2: Add Environment Variables
1. Go to **Variables** tab
2. Add all your environment variables
3. Deploy automatically triggers

### Option C: Render (Great Alternative)

#### Step 1: Connect Repository
1. Go to [render.com](https://render.com)
2. Connect your GitHub repo
3. Choose **Web Service**

#### Step 2: Configure
- **Build Command**: `npm install`
- **Start Command**: `npm start`
- **Environment**: Add all variables

